    <summary>Specifies the CICP (Coding-Independent Code Points) color primaries for a color space, as defined in ITU-T H.273.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKColorspacePrimariesCicp` enumerates color primaries values as defined in ITU-T H.273 (CICP). These values identify the chromaticity coordinates of the red, green, and blue primaries for a color space. Use this enum with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp*> to create a color space from CICP parameters.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create an sRGB-compatible color space using CICP parameters
var colorSpace = SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(
    SKColorspacePrimariesCicp.Rec709,
    SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp.Iec6196621);
```
]]></format></remarks>
